Dengue/DHF - Honduras: background 19991017.1843
[1
Date: 14 Sep 2000 19:01:58 EDT
From: Kathleen Dunleavy <HEYTHLEEN@aol.com>
Source: CNN 14 Sep 2000 [edited
<http://www.cnn.com/2000/HEALTH/09/14/salvador.dengue.ap/index.html>

SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) -- President Francisco Flores declared a
national emergency this week after an epidemic of dengue fever claimed a
17th victim.
Flores urged Salvadorans to take action to stop the epidemic's spread,
including trying to eliminate mosquito-breeding places in populated areas.
"I feel this measure will help awaken the population," Flores said.
The action came after a child under the age of 5 died early Tuesday,
becoming the epidemic's 17th victim. The country's Ministry of Health also
said officials were investigating the deaths of 3 other children to
determine if they also were killed by dengue.
Puerto Rican and U.S. scientists are in El Salvador studying the epidemic.
Dengue has infected more than 750 Salvadorans, mostly children, this year.
Last year, it killed 3 people in El Salvador.
--
Kathleen Dunleavy
IEC Centrifuges
<HEYTHLEEN@aol.com>
