[2
Date: 14 Sep 2000 17:13:10 -0400
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: Agencia EFE, Story Filed 14 Sep 2000 1:58 PM EST [edited

HONDURAS DECLARES NATIONAL DENGUE FEVER ALERT
-------------------------------------------------
Tegucigalpa, Sep 14, 2000 (EFE via COMTEX) -- The number of cases of
hemorrhagic dengue fever increased to 19, Honduran Deputy Health Minister
Elliethe Giron said Thursday, announcing a national alert as an epidemic
sweeps neighboring El Salvador.
However, the 7 new cases reported in Honduras are unrelated to the epidemic
in El Salvador, Giron noted. Of the 7 new cases of hemorrhagic dengue, 6
occurred in Tegucigalpa and one in Cedros, in the interior of the country,
adding to the 12 reported last week. Among these 19 cases, only one adult
was involved, the rest were children, and none have died.
Giron did not link the growing incidence of the illness in Honduras to the
crisis situation in El Salvador, where 16 have died and officials have
reported 221 cases of hemorrhagic dengue fever and 1 875 cases of common
dengue.
